<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-11674] oneByteBuf in CryptoInputStream and CryptoOutputStream should be non static</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-11674</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A common optimization in the io classes for Input/Output Streams is to save a single length-1 byte array to use in single byte read/write calls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CryptoInputStream and CryptoOutputStream both attempt to follow this practice but mistakenly mark the array as static. That means that only a single instance of each can be present in a JVM safely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
